{ "bugs": [

  {
    "id": 1,
    "description": "In the `safeMultiply` method for `long` and `int`, there is no handling for the case when `val2` is a very large positive number. This could lead to an `ArithmeticException` when multiplying a large `val1` by a large `val2`."
  },

  {
    "id": 2,
    "description": "In the `safeMultiply` method for `long` and `long`, there is no handling for the case when both `val1` and `val2` are `Long.MIN_VALUE`. This could lead to an `ArithmeticException` when multiplying `-1` by `-1`."
  },

  {
    "id": 3,
    "description": "The `FieldUtils` class is declared as `final`, but it has a non-private constructor. This violates the principle of encapsulation and could potentially allow subclasses to be created."
  },

  {
    "id": 4,
    "description": "The `safeNegate` method throws an `ArithmeticException` when trying to negate `Integer.MIN_VALUE`, but it should throw an `IllegalArgumentException` because the input value is not valid for the operation."
  }

] }
